    question: "How long does training take?",
    answer: "Training typically takes 5-10 minutes (7K iterations) to 30-45 minutes (30K iterations) depending on quality settings and GPU. A fast 7K iteration run takes ~5-10 minutes, while a high-quality 30K iteration run takes ~30-45 minutes on a modern GPU."
  },
  {
    question: "What is densification in 3DGS?",
    answer: "Densification is the process of adding Gaussians during training. The algorithm clones Gaussians in under-reconstructed regions and splits them in over-reconstructed regions, adapting the representation to scene complexity."
  }
];

